article.headline: North Texas 74, Arkansas St. 63
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Collin Dennis went 4-for-6 from long distance Thursday night and finished with 30 points to lead North Texas to a 74-63 victory over Arkansas State. Dennis also made 12 of 15 free-throw attempts for NTSU (11-4, 2-2 Sun Belt Conference). ASU (7-8, 2-3) trailed 32-24 at the half. Ben Bell added 10 points for North Texas, while the Mean Green's Quincy Williams was the only rebounder in double digits, grabbing 13. Ryan Wedel led ASU with 17 points. Adrian Banks added 11 points and Yima Chia-Kur scored 10.
